habitat_description:
The range of the river cooter is from Maryland to the Florida Panhandle and northwestern peninsular Florida, west to eastern Texas, eastern Oklahoma, and eastern Kansas, north to Missouri, Illinois, Indiana, and the Ohio River valley of West Virginia, south to the Gulf Coast (Conant and Collins 1991; Dreslik 1998; Seidel and Dreslik 1996). Habitats include streams with moderate current, abundant aquatic vegetation, basking sites, and rocky bottom; as well lakes, ponds, oxbows, swamps, large ditches, lagoons, brackish tidal marshes (Ernst and Barbour 1972).

Burrows in or using soil, fallen logs or debris; leaves water only to bask or nest (Ernst and Barbour 1972).Eggs are laid in nests dug in sandy soil usually less than about 30 m from water (Ernst and Barbour 1972).
